az vm config datadisk add

Add a VM Data Disk.

USAGE:

az vm config datadisk add [--vm] <vm> [--name] <name> [--vhdUri] <vhdUri> [[--caching] <caching>] [--diskSizeInGB] <diskSizeInGB> [[--lun] <lun>] [--createOption] <createOption> [[--sourceImageUri] <sourceImageUri>]

PARAMETERS:

--caching
  [string] The virtual machine data disk's caching.

--createOption
  [string] The virtual machine data disk's create option.

--diskSizeInGB
  [int32] The virtual machine data disk's size in GB.

--lun
  [int32] The virtual machine data disk's Lun.

--name
  [string] The virtual machine data disk's name.

--sourceImageUri (--sourceImage)
  [string] The virtual machine OS disk's source image Uri.

--vhdUri
  [string] The virtual machine data disk's Vhd Uri.

--vm (--vmProfile)
  [object] The virtual machine profile. You may use commands including 'az vm config create' or 'az vm bootdiagnostics ls' or 'az vm ls' or 'az vm config additionalunattendcontent add' to produce a VM. You can pipe the output of one of these commands to the input of this command, or you can store the ouput to a file and use 'az vm config datadisk add --VM @@<file-name>' to pass the file contents. See 'Related Commands' for more information.

